ans law (logical AND or OR can be replaced by the other)','AND or OR may be replaced by the other....\r\n\r\nNOT(A OR B) ≡ (NOT A) AND (NOT B)\r\nNOT(A AND B) ≡ (NOT A) OR (NOT B)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, De Morgans law',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 14:23:49',1,1),(516,'Identify the symbols for NOT (¬), AND (^) and OR (⌵)','\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, AND expression, XOR expression, NOT expression',1,41,22,NULL,NULL,'','2019-01-22 15:41:32',1,1),(517,'Describe the Law of Distribution (multiplying and factoring out of an expression)','The Law of Distribution allows for the multiplying or factoring out of an expression.\r\n1) The OR distribution law: A AND (B OR C) ≡ (A AND B) OR (A AND C) \r\n2) The AND distribution law: A OR (B AND C) ≡ (A OR B) AND (A OR C)\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, Law of distribution',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 16:07:22',1,1),(518,'Describe the Law of Association (removal of brackets and regrouping)','The Law of Association states that the removal of brackets and regrouping of the variables.\r\n1) OR association law: A OR (B OR C) ≡ (A OR ) B OR C ≡ A OR B OR C \r\n2) AND association law: A AND (B AND C) ≡ (A AND B) AND C ≡ A AND B AND C\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, Law of association',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 16:14:19',1,1),(519,'Describe the Law of Commutation (The order of terms is not important)','The order of terms is not important\r\nA AND B ≡ B AND A\r\nA OR B ≡ B OR A\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, Law of commutation',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 16:16:47',1,1),(520,'Describe the Law of Double Negation (reversing something get you back where you started)','You end up back where you started...\r\nNOT(NOT A) ≡ A\r\n\r\n','boolean logic, law of double negation',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 16:30:03',1,1),(521,'Describe the Rule of Absorption (the second term inside the bracket can be eliminated by the term outside the bracket)','The second term inside the bracket can be eliminated by the term outside the bracket if the following terms apply....\r\n1. The operators inside and outside the brackets must be different\r\n2. The term outside the brackets must also be inside the brackets\r\nX OR (X AND Y) ≡ X\r\nX AND (X OR Y) = X\r\nA OR B ≡ B OR A\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, Law of absorption',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 16:37:36',1,1),(522,'Describe the General Rules of Boolean Algebra','There are 8 general rules for simplifying boolean algebraic expressions\r\n \r\nAND expressions\r\n\r\nRule 1: X AND 0 ≡ FALSE\r\nRule 2: X AND 1 ≡ X\r\nRule 3: X AND X ≡ X\r\nRule 4: X AND NOT X ≡ FALSE\r\nRule 5: X OR 0 ≡ X\r\nRule 6: X OR 1 ≡ TRUE\r\nRule 7: X OR X ≡ X\r\nRule 8: X OR NOT X ≡ TRUE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, General rules of boolean algebra',2,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 17:29:59',1,1),(523,'Simpify a boolean expression using a Karnaugh map','\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic',4,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-22 18:06:53',1,1),(524,'Construct a Karnaugh map to simplify an expression (two-variable problem and three-variable problem)','Rules for K-Map\r\n1) A group must only contain 1s\r\n2) A group can only be horizontal or vertical, not diagonal\r\n3) A group must contain 1, 2, 4, 8... (2^n 1s)\r\n4) Groups should be as large as possible\r\n5) Groups may overlap\r\n6) Groups can wraparound\r\n7) Every 1 must be in at least one group\r\n8) There should be few groups as possible\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Boolean logic, Karnaugh map, Circuits',4,41,22,NULL,NULL,'Simplifying','2019-01-23 05:13:18',1,1),(525,'Define the term half adder','Half adders take two-bit input, perform an addition and output a 1-bit result and 1-bit carry.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Half adder, Binary logic, Binary addition, Logic circuit',1,40,22,NULL,NULL,'Adders','2019-01-26 04:30:45',1,1),(526,'Define the term full adder','A full adder consists of two half adders. It takes two-inputs plus a