emory','Volatile means that RAM loses data if the power is switched off whereas ROM is non-volatile meaning that if the power is switched off the data is not lost.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Non-volatile Memory,Volatile Memory,Random Access Memory (RAM)',2,8,47,NULL,NULL,'','2019-02-11 14:50:50',1,1),(560,'Explain the Fetch-Decode-Execute cycle carried out by the CPU (Central Processing Unit)','When you open a program the instructions and data of the program are loaded into the main memory or RAM. The CPU fetches each instruction from main memory, it looks up the code in an instruction set and executes that instruction. The execution may also require data fetching from main memory.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Central Processing Unit (CPU),Registers,Random Access Memory (RAM),Fetch Decode Execute (FDE)',3,7,47,NULL,NULL,'','2019-02-12 04:35:06',1,1),(561,'Identify different types of network hardware','A network is made up of different network components. The main ones are Workstation, Server, Switch or Hub.\r\n','Switch, Hub, Client-server Network, Workstation, Network server',2,17,46,NULL,NULL,'','2019-02-18 12:53:22',1,1),(562,'Describe how search engines index web pages','Search engines look at the visible content and use metadata tags (keywords and description attributes) not visible to the user.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Metadata,HTML tags,Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML)',2,36,26,NULL,NULL,'','2019-02-20 15:13:24',1,1),(563,'Describe Googles Page Rank algorithm','Googles PageRank represents the web as a directed graph where the web page is a node and the edge represented as hyperlinks. The weighting of the edge is calculated by the PageRank algorithm.\r\n','Directed Graph,Googles PageRank',2,36,26,NULL,NULL,'','2019-02-21 04:43:08',1,1),(564,'Give a list of six factors affecting search results','Among the factors affecting search results are keywords in the metadata, the metadata description, keywords in the <TITLE> tag; the last update, the number of times a keyword appears in the 