'Construct and trace an algorithms written using iteration and recursion','Write and compare iterative and recursive algorithms, such as ones that produce a list of Factorial sequences - one using iteration and one using recursion. Write an algorithm that carries out traversal.\r\n\r\n','Recursive,Iteration',4,48,19,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-09 07:15:14',1,1),(592,'Identify and name the four standard flow chart symbols','The four standard flow chart shapes are Start/Stop, Input/Output, Action and Descision.','Flow chart',1,36,42,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-09 11:42:02',1,1),(593,'Follow a simple flow chart that includes the four standard flow chart symbols','\r\n\r\n','Flow chart',2,36,42,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-09 11:44:13',1,1),(594,'Create a simple flow chart from a given list of instructions','Given a list of instructions create a flow chart using the four standard flowchart shapes: start/stop, input/output, action and decision.\r\n','Flow chart',3,36,42,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-09 11:45:52',1,1),(595,'Construct a flow chart to solve a given problem using decision symbols with appropriate inputs and output','Using a simulator, such as Flowol, solve different problems. Demonstrate the use of problem solving techniques such as decomposition to break down the problem and solve one problem at a time and use pattern recognition to avoid repeating yourself.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Flow chart,Decomposition,Pattern recognition',4,36,42,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-09 11:48:23',1,1),(596,'Describe the four offences under the Computer Misuse Act and the penalty for committing each offence','The four offences under the <b>Computer Misuse Act</b> increase in seriousness from unauthorised access to computer material to helping someone else to carrywriting viruses. The first is unauthorised access to computer material, which carries up to a <b>six month</b> prison sentence and/or a large fine. The second is the intent to commit a crime, such as <b>fraud</b> or <b>blackmail</b> and the third unauthorised modification (changing or deleting) <b>data</b>. The second and third offence under the Computer Misuse Act both carry a <b>five year</b> prison sentence and/or a hefty fine. The fourth offence is making, supplying or obtaining anything which can be used to carry out misuse offence, such as <b>viruses</b> and malware which carry a <b>ten year</b> prison sentence and/or a <b>unlimited</b> fine. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Computer Misuse Act,Computer virus,Malware,Ransomware',2,67,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-14 11:54:53',1,1),(597,'Formulate a discussion that relate cases and prosecutions under the Computer Misuse Act','Formulate a presentation to discuss court cases where people or groups of people have been prosecuted under the Computer Misuse Act. What are the impacts on the lives of those who have been prosecuted or could be prosecuted under the Computer Misuse Act.\r\n','Computer Misuse Act',4,67,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-14 12:16:44',1,1),(598,'Give examples of different measures you can put in place to prevent unauthorised access to your computer, phone and social media accounts','(1) Use up to date antivirus software. (2) Never reply to anonymous emails. (3) Use filtering software on email accounts.  (4) Use strong passwords. (5) Never give someone else your personal information, user names and password.','',2,67,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-14 12:44:08',1,1),(599,'Construct a program that uses a static array and a dynamic array to update and append data','An array is a static data structure used if you know the number of items being stored in the data structure will not change. A list is a dynamic data structure that is used if new items are likely to added to the data structure (NOTE: Python only supports lists).\r\n\r\n','Array,One-dimensional array,Two-dimensional array',4,45,2,3,NULL,'Arrays','2019-03-15 14:25:33',1,1),(600,'Refine the top-down design into testable elements','\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Valid extreme,Invalid,Invalid extreme,Validation,White box testing,Black box Testing',4,49,19,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-23 12:41:02',1,1),(601,'Describe key structures of the program that will be tested','\r\n\r\n','Subroutine,Function,Procedure',2,49,19,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-23 12:46:07',1,1),(602,'Explain how different parts of the program will tested during and after development','\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','White box testing,Black box Testing,User Acceptance Testing (UAT)',3,49,19,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-23 13:02:57',1,1),(603,'Explain how black box testing will be carried out after development','\r\n','Black box Testing',3,49,19,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-23 13:05:20',1,1),(604,'Explain reasons for not giving out personal information and sending photos of yourself online','\r\n\r\n\r\n','Privacy',3,30,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 07:17:09',1,1),(605,'Give examples of personal information','\r\n\r\n','Privacy,Personal information',2,30,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 07:18:06',1,1),(606,'Identify actions to take in order to stay safe online','\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','',1,30,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 07:22:57',1,1),(607,'Describe what is meant by malicious software','Malware is a program that has been <b>installed</b> on your <b>computer</b> without you knowing. Your computer may be infected by Malware through downloads from <b>websites</b> or attachments in <b>emails</b> designed to trick you.','Malware',2,27,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 12:38:14',1,1),(608,'Give examples of malicious software','\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Malware,Internet bot,Rootkit,Spyware,Trojan horse,Worm,Ransomware,Keylogger',2,27,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 12:56:58',1,1),(609,'Identify online dangers','\r\n','Malware,Phishing',1,27,50,NULL,NULL,'','2019-03-24 12:58:32',1,1),(610,'Give an account of how records in one table related to records in another table (Primary Key and Foreign Key relationship)','\r\n\r\n','Foreign key,Primary key,Structured Query Language (SQL)',2,46,4,NULL,NULL,'SQL','2019-03-29 11:41:45',1,1),(611,'Describe how to search for a value using a hash table','Pass the key to the hash function and go to the array index in list. If the value is not found follow the linked list until the value is found.\r\n\r\n','Hash table,Linked list',2,36,21,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 04:30:07',1,1),(612,'Describe how to insert a value into a hash table','Pass the key to the hash function and go to the array index in the list. If the location is empty then insert the value or follow the linked list a free space is found.\r\n','Hash table',2,36,21,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 04:30:39',1,1),(613,'Describe how to delete a value from a hash table','Pass the key to the hash function and go to the array index in the list. If the value is not found, follow the linked list until the value is found.them mark the entry then update the pointers\r\n','Hash table',2,36,21,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 04:31:28',1,1),(614,'Create a hash function to select, insert and delete values from a list','Combine the use of a linked list and hash function. Use decomposition to create a hashing function and pass the value to find the values in the linked list.\r\n','Hash table',4,36,21,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 04:32:27',1,1),(615,'Explain how hash function turns a string into a integer used to select, insert and delete values from a list','Hashing is the process of creating value from a given input. The output','Hash function',3,36,22,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 04:46:13',1,1),(616,'State the purpose of using hash tables to retrieve data','A hash table allows for the fast retrieval of data by calculating the index value from the value being searched.','Hash function,Hash table',1,36,21,NULL,NULL,'','2019-04-10 05:28:59',1,1),(617,'Describe the concurrent processing and parallel processing','Parallel processing refers to the more than one instruction being processed by different processors whereas concurrent processing refers to each process being given a slice of time processor time.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Concurrent processing,Parallel processing',2,48,25,NULL,NULL,'Concurrency','2019-05-03 04:04:36',1,1),(618,'Explain the advantages and disadvantages of concurrent processing','The benefit of concurrent processing is that more tasks can be completed in a given time. For example, the time waiting for a user to input data or view data from output. However, if there are many users trying to run programs that involve a lot of computation, the programs take longer to complete. Processes also compete with each other for processing time.\r\n\r\n','Concurrent processing',3,48,25,NULL,NULL,'Concurrency','2019-05-03 04:19:04',1,1),(619,'Explain the advantages and disadvantages of parallel processing','In parallel processing, tasks can be performed simultaneously such as when performing large amounts of repetitive calculations on large data sets.  However, there is an overhead in coordinating tasks.\r\n\r\n','Parallel processing',3,48,25,NULL,NULL,'Concurrency','2019-05-03 04:25:32',1,1),(620,'Explain how caching is used to increases response time in processing','Caching is the temporary storage of instructions or data that may be needed again shortly. By storing the instructions or data closer to the processor the faster they can be retrieved next time they are needed. Another example is caching of web pages, javascript or CSS files on your local computer rather than downloading them every time the page is refreshed (or if the page is visited frequently).\r\n\r\n','Caching',3,48,25,NULL,NULL,'Caching','2019-05-03 04:41:33',1,1),(621,'Describe the drawbacks of caching','Algorithms to predict which data should be cached can be quite complicated. If the incorrect data is cached this needs to be refreshed with the correct data.\r\n','Caching',2,48,25,NULL,NULL,'Caching','2019-05-03 04:52:45',1,1),(622,'Describe different uses of shortest path algorithms','\r\n\r\n\r\n','A* algorithm,Dijkstras algorithm',2,39,22,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-14 08:26:02',1,1),(623,'Explain how Dijkstras algorithm is used to traverse a graph to find the shortest path','\r\n\r\n','Breadth-first Traversal,Dijkstras algorithm',3,39,22,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-14 08:27:30',1,1),(624,'Explain how A* algorithm is a special case path-finding algorithm','The A* algorithm is an extension of Dijkstras algorithm. It has two cost functions to measure the distance: The first, like in Dijkstras algorithm, is the real cost from the node to a given node and the second is a hueristic function to give an estimated cost, whose aim is to reach the destination by giving nodes that take a path in the direction of the destination a higher priority.','A* algorithm,Heuristic method',3,39,22,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-14 08:31:47',1,1),(625,'Describe how a program is allocated to a space in memory','A program is allocated a specific area of memory while the program is running. In multitasking environment, multiple programs are stored in memory.\r\n','Memory',2,32,25,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-16 07:59:41',1,1),(626,'Explain the differences and similarities between paging and segmentation','Paging and Segmentation are methods used to manage programs in memory. Paging divides the memory into fixed size pages of 4mb. If the program needs to occupy more than 4mb of memory the program may occupy non-contiguous pages, but this slows down the program. Segmentation stores the program into logically sized data blocks, dividing the program by its functions and modules. Unlike paging, this allows the program to execute as a logical block of code. However, it is more difficult to load the program as the RAM gets full.  \r\n\r\n','Paging,Segmentation',3,32,25,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-16 08:05:24',1,1),(627,'Describe the purpose of protocol in data communications','The rules set out by TCP/IP protocol stack are required in order for data communications to work between devices. Each layer of the TCP/IP protocol stack consists of a number of protocols. The TCP/IP protocol stack is based on the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) Model.\r\n\r\n\r\n','TCP/IP Protocol Stack',2,25,26,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-17 05:04:39',1,1),(628,'Describe how the various protocols operate at each layer in the stack','The TCP/IP stack consists of four layers: The Application layer, Transport Layer, Internet layer and Link Layer. Each layer consists of a set of protocols which have different roles.  As the data is passed from one layer to the other the data is encapsulated in an envelope.\r\n','TCP/IP Protocol Stack,Application Layer,Transport Layer,Internet Layer,Link Layer',2,25,26,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-17 05:13:53',1,1),(629,'Describe the different sections of a segment of memory given to a process','The memory segment given to the process is divided into four sections which are allocated for a given purpose: The Code segment contains the program instructions\\\\\\; The Data segment contains variables\\\\\\; The Stack segment allows the program to use functions and subroutines\\\\\\; The Free memory space allows the stack to grow or shrink.\r\n','Segmentation',2,32,25,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-22 06:46:45',1,1),(630,'Give an account of what causes a memory leak','A memory leak occurs when a program does not unallocate memory for use by other processes.\r\n','Memory leak',2,32,25,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-22 06:58:14',1,1),(631,'Give an account of the cause of a stack overflow','Each time the program calls a function (or calls itself) it is added to the stack. A stack overflow occurs when the stack runs out of memory.','Stack overflow',2,32,26,NULL,NULL,'','2019-05-22 07:02:17',1,1);
