INSERT INTO `sow_lesson_plan` VALUES (1,163,1,'Review the test plan from the exemplar','Identify a number of tests from the exemplar (High exemplar pg 270 - 275). How is the program being tested? What types of tests are being carried out?',10,'fa-door-open'),(2,163,4,'Black-box testing test plan','Write a test plan (High Exemplar pg 42) to check the functionality of the program against the end user requirements.',10,'fa-user'),(3,163,3,'White-box testing','From the top-down design state the data that will be used to test the program. Identify an element to be tested. For example, if you have an element of your program which receives an input from the user, state the data that you will use to test it (Med exemplar pg 53). Where applicable, use normal, extreme and borderline data. Can the elements be tested without a GUI? How can you design the program as testable elements? ',10,'fa-user'),(4,163,6,'Roles and responsibilities of testing','What is the difference between white-box testing and black-box testing? Who carries out Alpha testing? Who carries out Beta Testing?',5,'fa-door-closed'),(5,163,2,'Test strategy headings','Create subheadings: Testing during development, Post development testing, Acceptance testing. ',5,'fa-user'),(6,163,5,'Acceptance testing questionnaire','Create a questionnaire for the end user to evaluate whether they think the program has met their requirements',10,'fa-user'),(7,167,1,'What is phishing?','Research: What is phishing?',10,'fa-door-open'),(8,167,2,'What is personal Information?','Write down examples of personal information. Share with the rest of the class.',10,'fa-user'),(11,167,5,'Staying safe quiz','1) When I’m on line I should never give out my last name, address, phone number, the name of my school, or teams I play for.  2) I can send a photo of myself online when I’ve told my parents and they’ve given me permission to do so. 3) If someone I meet online gives me his phone number I should ask my parents permission before I call. 4) If someone send me an inappropriate message or materials I should immediately do not reply to it and save it, tell my parents, use the report button. 5) If someone I’ve met online wants to meet in person I should never consider doing so before talking to my parents about it',15,'fa-door-closed'),(12,167,3,'Sharing photos','What are the dangers of posting pictures of yourself online? CEOP KS3 Film Consequences https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZSMi7ftfalA',15,'fa-comments'),(13,167,4,'Contacting someone you have met online','Should you contact or meet someone you have met online',5,'fa-comments'),(14,166,4,'Trace tables','Complete the trace tables',15,'fa-user'),(16,166,2,'Purpose of testing','What is the purpose of testing?',5,'fa-comments'),(17,166,5,'Exam Question','Answer the questions on White-box testing, Black-box testing and acceptance testing',15,'fa-door-closed'),(18,166,3,'Stages of testing','Write down headings: Developer testing, Black-box testing, White-box testing, User Acceptance Testing',15,'fa-user'),(19,168,1,'iLOVEYOU virus','What is the iLOVEYOU virus? When did it start? How did it spread? How was it so effective? How was it stopped?',15,'fa-door-open'),(20,168,3,'Protection against computer viruses','How can you protect yourself against computer viruses? In pairs find different ways of protecting your computer against viruses such as iLOVEYOU.',20,'fa-user-friends'),(21,168,4,'Online safety quiz','Answer the questions of what is a virus and how to protect against viruses',10,'fa-door-closed'),(22,168,2,'Types of viruses','Research different types of viruses',10,'fa-user'),(23,169,1,'SQL Select WHERE clause','Write SQL statements using the WHERE clause to SELECT records from a table',10,'fa-door-open'),(24,169,2,'Introduction to INNER JOIN','Show example of inner join using w3schools example (https://www.w3schools.com/sql/sql_join_inner.asp) of orders and customers table. Student to write join.',15,'fa-comments'),(25,169,3,'INNER JOIN','Student to create join between orders table and orderdetails table',20,'fa-user'),(26,169,4,'Exam-style Question','Question from assessment.',10,'fa-door-closed'),(27,160,1,'Global and local variables','Recap on local and global variables. Show video.',10,'fa-door-open'),(28,160,2,'Stack overflow','Show recursion which will cause a stack overflow. Predict outcome.',5,'fa-user'),(29,160,3,'Demonstrate a simple recursive function','Write a recursive function with a stop condition. Exceed recursion depth',10,'fa-user-friends'),(30,160,5,'Compare iteration and recursion','Compare  factorial function using iteration vs recursion',10,'fa-comments'),(31,160,6,'Perfornance and memory','Discuss performance and memory. Simple recursion with',15,'fa-comments'),(32,160,4,'Compare parameters and global variables?','Look at the use of parameters and global variables in recursive functions',5,'fas fa-question-circle'),(33,160,7,'Homework','Iteration and Recursion worksheet',5,'fa-door-closed');
